## Real-Time Event Flow (Sequence)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant P1 as Player 1 (Browser)
    participant SIO as Socket.io /battle
    participant MM as Matchmaking (Redis)
    participant DB as PostgreSQL
    participant BQ as BullMQ
    participant JW as Judge Worker

    P1->>SIO: battle:join_queue {difficulty, category}
    SIO->>MM: Add to sorted set (score = timestamp)
    Note over MM: Another player P2 joins same filters
    MM-->>SIO: Match found! (P1 + P2)
    SIO->>DB: Create Battle + 2 BattleParticipants
    SIO->>DB: Pick random Problem matching filters
    SIO-->>P1: battle:matched {battleId, problem, opponent, timer}
    SIO-->>P1: Join Socket room "battle:{battleId}"

    loop Every keystroke (throttled ~300ms)
        P1->>SIO: battle:code_change {battleId, code, cursor}
        SIO-->>P1: battle:opponent_typing {code snippet preview, cursor}
    end

    loop Chat messages
        P1->>SIO: battle:chat {battleId, message}
        SIO-->>P1: battle:chat_message {from, message, timestamp}
    end

    P1->>SIO: battle:submit {battleId, code}
    SIO->>DB: Create Submission
    SIO->>BQ: Enqueue judge job
    BQ->>JW: Execute in sandbox
    JW-->>BQ: Result
    BQ-->>SIO: (Redis Pub/Sub) battle:submission_result
    SIO-->>P1: battle:submission_result {passed, total, runtime}

    Note over SIO: Timer expires OR both submit
    SIO-->>P1: battle:ended {winner, scores}
    SIO->>DB: Update Battle status, winner
```

