## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Matchmaking Filters**: The plan assumes matching by `difficulty` + `category`. Should we also support matching by specific language preference, or let both players use whatever language they want on the shared problem?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Code Visibility**: Two options for "can see other guy is typing":
> 1. **Full mirror** — opponent sees your exact code in a read-only Monaco editor pane (like Google Docs)
> 2. **Blurred preview** — opponent sees a blurred/obfuscated version of your code (line count, typing indicator, progress bar) but not the actual logic
> 
> Option 2 is recommended for competitive integrity. Option 1 is better for learning/collaboration mode.

> [!WARNING]
> **Timer Authority**: The timer MUST be server-authoritative (not client-side). The server tracks `battle.startedAt` + `battle.durationSeconds` and broadcasts `battle:tick` events. Clients display the server's remaining time. This prevents cheating.

